OL,7,FGemma Gillett, for Tower Hamlets
OL,8,FCouncil, who brought the case,
OL,9,Fpreviously told the court: "It is
OL,10,Fclear that the property was, and had
OL,11,Fbeen considerably for some time,
OL,12,Fgrossly overcrowded.
OL,14,F"The information available suggests
OL,15,Fthat some 23 people were in occupation
OL,16,Fof the flat. One of the occupants was
OL,17,Ftaken to hospital and subsequently
OL,18,Fdied."
