OL,7,FRahman, who collected the rent and was
OL,8,Fthe person responsible for the
OL,9,Fproperty, pleaded guilty to one count
OL,10,Fof each of these three offences.
OL,12,FThey failed to allow regular
OL,13,Finspections, did not have a current
OL,14,Fgas certificate and did not produce
OL,15,Fthe documents required of them as the
OL,16,Fcontroller or manager of the property.
OL,18,FAfter the fire, Rahman told a liaison
OL,19,Fofficer that he rented the flat to two
OL,20,Fpeople and he did not know who the
OL,21,Fothers were.
